'''''Here's How''''' is an unproduced ''[[Star Wars]]''-themed educational television show and comic strip for children.

Developed by [[Lucasfilm]] Special Project Manager [[Jok Church]] in the mid-1980s, ''Here's How'' would have featured [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] teaching a foreign language and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] explaining the physical science of real-world objects. Despite initial interest from Lucasfilm, the project was ultimately abandoned.

Church went on to create [[Wikipedia:You Can With Beakman and Jax|You Can With Beakman and Jax]], a weekly syndicated newspaper strip (later [[Wikipedia:Beakman's World|adapted for television]]) that, similar to the premise for ''Here's How'', taught children about science in an entertaining fashion.

